![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/0bd0429a-880a-40e3-91d4-7d7ad623eb04/382.jpg)

What happens when the world’s greatest villains masquerade as its most beloved heroes? In this week’s episode of the _Major Issues Podcast_, the gang dives deep into the first 9 issues of _Dark Avengers_ by Brian Michael Bendis and Mike Deodato Jr.! Spinning out of the events of _Secret Invasion_, Norman Osborn has been handed the keys to the kingdom—and he wastes no time assembling a twisted version of the Avengers filled with killers, manipulators, and madmen. We break down the deception, power plays, and psychological warfare that make this title a defining chapter of Marvel’s “Dark Reign” era. From Sentry’s instability to Moonstone’s manipulation, and Ares’ reluctant involvement to Osborn’s descent into madness—nothing is off-limits. Join us as we explore what happens when the line between hero and villain is completely shattered!  
  
Please leave us a **_review_** on [**ITunes**](https://podcasts.apple.com/us/podcast/major-issues-podcast/id1321720972) so we can grow our audience and grow as podcasters! Rate us wherever podcasts are found. Don't forget to check out our merchandise! All episodes of Major Issues are brought to you by **ComicBook Clique**, the only stop for the latest and greatest things to come to comic books and comic book media.

